{"id":"core-roads-wheels","name":"Core Collection \u2014 Roads & Wheels","version":"1.0","publisher":"DiceForge Studios Ltd.","description":"11 vehicles \u2014 Civilian ground vehicles from bicycles to semi-trucks. Reference implementations from the Savage Worlds core rules covering every era of road transport.","weapons":[],"mods":[],"specials":[],"vehicles":[{"name":"Bicycle","size":-1,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Two wheels, no motor, no armour, no dignity. Half of all shots hit the rider instead.","notes":"The bicycle is invisible. Nobody notices one more cyclist on a city street, which makes it the perfect surveillance and courier vehicle for low-tech campaigns. In chase scenes, she squeezes through gaps no car can follow \u2014 alleys, stairwells, crowded markets. 50% of shots hit the rider rather than the vehicle.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":-3,"handlingLevel":0,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["open_top"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":16},{"name":"Horse-Drawn Carriage","size":3,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Four wheels, one horse, variable passenger comfort. Stagecoaches, hansoms, and broughams all fall here.","notes":"The carriage covers everything from open farm carts to enclosed broughams and four-horse stagecoaches. She's your chase vehicle for historical and fantasy campaigns \u2014 highway robberies, runaway horses, rooftop leaps onto the luggage rack. Variants include the fast but fragile hansom cab, the armoured prison wagon, and the heavy freight coach. Horse-drawn, so she stops when the horses do.","toughLevel":-1,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":-3,"handlingLevel":-3,"woundsLevel":-1,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["open_top","towing"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":16},{"name":"Early Automobile","size":3,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Crank-start, top-heavy, and terrifying at speed. Model Ts, Tin Lizzies, and their ilk.","notes":"This covers the first generation of motor cars \u2014 Model Ts, Austin Sevens, Citro\u00ebn Type As, and their contemporaries. Slow, temperamental, and revolutionary. She puts your campaign on wheels for the first time: Prohibition rum-runners, early pulp adventures, the first getaway cars. Unreliable enough that a failed Repair roll at the worst possible moment is practically a genre convention.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":-2,"handlingLevel":-2,"woundsLevel":-1,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","temperamental"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":40},{"name":"Street Motorcycle","size":1,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Stock road bike \u2014 Harleys, Ducatis, or the local equivalent. Fast, exposed, and half the shots hit the rider.","notes":"Stock road bikes from any era \u2014 Harley-Davidsons, Triumphs, Ducatis, BMWs, or Honda CBs depending on your setting. She splits lanes, threads traffic, and fits where cars can't follow. The rider is fully exposed \u2014 50% of shots hit them rather than the bike. That vulnerability is the price of agility. Consider whether your setting's bikers ride in gangs, because a pack of motorcycles in a chase changes the dynamic entirely.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":0,"woundsLevel":-1,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["open_top"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":1,"mphOverride":120},{"name":"Off-Road Motorcycle","size":0,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Knobby tyres, excellent suspension, questionable life choices. Trail bikes, enduros, and motocross machines.","notes":"Trail bikes, enduros, motocross machines, and military despatch riders' mounts. She goes where roads don't \u2014 jungle recon, desert patrol, mountain courier runs. Think of everything from Steve McQueen's fence jump to modern special forces insertion by dirt bike. Treats each inch of Difficult Ground as 1.5 inches instead of 2 inches, same as four-wheel drive.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":-2,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":0,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["open_top","all_terrain","four_wd"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":80},{"name":"Compact Car","size":4,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Economy hatchback. Honda Civics, Ford Fiestas, and a thousand forgettable commuter boxes.","notes":"Every economy hatchback ever made \u2014 Honda Civics, Ford Fiestas, VW Golfs, Toyota Corollas. She's the default civilian vehicle. Every NPC drives one, every car park is full of them, every car chase starts or ends with one crumpled against a lamppost. Mechanically unremarkable, which is exactly the point \u2014 she's the baseline everything else is measured against.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":0,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":1,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":120},{"name":"Mid-Size Sedan","size":4,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Four doors, air bags, reasonable legroom. Your Camrys, Accords, and fleet rental staples.","notes":"Your Camrys, Accords, Passats, and fleet rental staples. She carries more passengers and gear than the compact, handles roughly the same, and blends into traffic just as easily. Also covers unmarked police cars, taxi cabs, and the anonymous saloon your players steal when they need to move without attracting attention. The world's most forgettable getaway car.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":0,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","cargo_bay"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":4,"mphOverride":120},{"name":"Family Minivan","size":4,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Sliding doors, cup holders, existential surrender. The vehicle of parenthood.","notes":"Chrysler Voyagers, Toyota Previas, VW Transporters, and their kin. She carries a full party plus gear \u2014 the team vehicle for modern campaigns, the thing everyone piles into when the job goes sideways. Not fast, not tough, but she holds everyone and their equipment in one vehicle. Sliding side doors make boarding and exiting faster than a four-door sedan.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":0,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","cargo_bay"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":7,"mphOverride":90},{"name":"Sport Utility Vehicle","size":5,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Four-wheel drive, luxury features, poor fuel economy. Range Rovers to Cherokees.","notes":"Range Rovers, Jeep Cherokees, Toyota Land Cruisers, Ford Explorers. She bridges civilian comfort and rough terrain capability. Four-wheel drive gets her off-road where sedans can't follow. The vehicle of choice for private military contractors, safari guides, rural law enforcement, and players who expect trouble outside city limits. Treats Difficult Ground as 1.5 inches per inch.","toughLevel":1,"armourLevel":0,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","four_wd","all_terrain"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":7,"mphOverride":120},{"name":"Sports Car","size":4,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Two doors, low profile, speed over practicality. Mustangs, Camaros, and mid-life crises.","notes":"Mustangs, Camaros, Porsches, Ferraris, Corvettes, and every mid-life crisis on four wheels. She wins chases through raw speed and sharp handling. Fast on straights, nimble in corners, and utterly useless off-road or in bad weather. The vehicle your players covet and the one that gets them into trouble. Two doors means getting into the back seat takes an action.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":0,"speedLevel":3,"handlingLevel":2,"woundsLevel":-2,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":3,"mphOverride":160},{"name":"Semi-Truck","size":9,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Cab and trailer. Peterbilts, Kenworths, Scanias \u2014 the kings of the motorway.","notes":"Peterbilts, Kenworths, Scanias, Volvos, and every long-haul cab that's ever jackknifed across a motorway. She can't manoeuvre, she can't hide, and she takes a long time to stop. But she carries anything, tows anything, and at highway speed she's an unstoppable battering ram. The trailer itself is roughly Size 7, Toughness 14(2) \u2014 big enough to serve as a mobile base or improvised roadblock.","toughLevel":-1,"armourLevel":0,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":1,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","cargo_bay","towing","loud"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-4,"passengers":1,"mphOverride":75}]}